caption: Just got my uber eats order. Ordered shrimp Pad Thai and they sent Tofu Pad Thai. The receipt reads Shrimp. What went wrong?
Great service, great food!
Food is delicious
Delicious and authentic Thai food. Got duck noodle soup and lard salad which were both delicious. Pick up process was fast and easy. Can't wait to come back to try more things!

First time here ! I usually try to order food that is not common seen. So I order the duck noodle soup with the wide rice noodle. It was delicious and flavorful . If you like the heavy flavor this is your dish. Imagine, the Peking duck add a soup and noodle that is the flavor. We came here with a big group got their pad Thai , curry and pad sew. All pretty good and the group like it. The only thing I wasn't that impress is the dessert, I order the coconut tapioca it was different than what I was expected.

Bathroom was decent. It all checks my boxes for chicken. However it's not the best chicken ever by any stretch of the imagination but it's good. I got the medium spice and i liked it. Sliders are HUGE but they also fall apart easy ( breading was rubbing off to make it even more messier.)

I was walking past this restaurant on Archer and took a glance at their menu that was taped to their window. I love really good Thai food, so I thought I would try it. It was delicious, filling and flavorful! I like to order things I have not tried before, so I ordered the Crazy Spicy Udon with chicken as my protein. It also came with an array of vegetables (which I love) of onion, green onion, carrots, baby corns, eggplant, sweet and hot peppers, basil leaves and bean sprouts. They also prepared enough that lasted me for three days. As a treat, I ordered a slice of the green tea cheesecake as well. It was delicious! They are extremely fast in there and I do know that they deliver and also use Postmates delivery. Check the website for the times, as I am not sure. I walked past there around 5:30 pm on a Friday.

The egg rolls were delicious, I ate them with the sweet and sour sauce. We also grabbed the chicken satay, the calamari was horrible.  The pepper steak was great, didn't like the sweet basil dish at all I had chicken and beef. I couldn't taste any garlic in that dish what a bummer. Overall they were ok. Sorry no photos this was a pick up order.
The last 2-3 times it has taken awhile (over an hour) to prepare the food, which has been disappointing especially because the food is great. Order early!
Omg the egg rolls was really good do yourselves a favor and get a least two orders
Great place authentic
The best Thai place around.
Love this place! They have large portions and the taste is great. I’ve had several of their dishes and enjoyed them all. I’ve only ordered through Uber eats and I’ve never been disappointed.
Food was good and the service was very good but the place could use a cleaning and some updating.
Definitely a place worth stopping by, the food is awesome and fresh, the pricing is fair and it is always neat in here. 5 stars.
The food here is actually really good. The portion size is large. I ordered off Uber eats and am very happy
When I order from here it is usually off of Uber Eats. The food is consistent and delicious.
It's not bad. I would go again.
The food is good and the people are cool

Excellent service.  Food is consistently delicious.  Love their pad see ew and Singapore noodles.  Used to live in the south loop and missed my local Thai restaurant. Now I’m so happy that I found this place!!

Hidden gem, highly recommend the PANANG CURRY and the Pad Kee Mao. Really great as veggie options. Always tastes fresh and is amazing for the price. - not so much the fried appetizers though, just skip those ;)
The food was delicious and I ate it all - Service is prompt. Definitely worth checking out.
Would absolutely recommend visiting this place. Awesome character, yummy food, awesome customer service. I recommend this place.
Good food
Good food, quick and friendly service!

Horrible horrible place. Ordered food and had a fre bites, bit down on something had, it was a small rock or piece of gravel. Cracked my tooth called the restaurant they didn't care one but called ubrr eats also didn't care. Will never order from here again!
Amazing place!!! That green curry is delicious!

Very happy we found this very small place while traveling through Chicago and looking for a good Thai meal. I have the lunch special will my boss had a regular entree and both of them were fantastic. I would highly recommend scouting this place out and checking out their food!
Love the Blue Frog for Lunch
Amazing Thai food at a great price

Terrible. There was hardly any beef in my pad Thai. 2 stringy shrimps in my Tom kha. There was no lemongrass or anything really in there otherwise just some mushrooms and that soup cost like 695. I'll never go back

Hey a Thai place in Bridgeport. Score! This place is easy to miss because it has a blue awning above it for Archer Cafe, but the window has a big, you guessed it, blue frog on it.  If you’re on the hunt for some fast and casual Thai, this is it. Reasonably priced, extremely fast turnaround, and pretty easy to get to. The place itself is small with only a few tables, so probably a hint that this is more of a delivery and pickup kind of joint.  I have to come back and try some other things on the menu, because there’s even pho on the menu. Not expecting much, but I’ll take what I can get.
Great food great service.
Pad Thai & basil fried rice are delicious
Love everything here!
Very small seating area. Almost passed it up because the awning says "Archer Cafe". Great tasting food, friendly, also byob which was great.

Disappointed and Duped is what we’ll title this review.  After being faithful patrons our most recent visit was the nail in the coffin. We waited forever for everything. Forever to order, to receive our food and then to get the check.  There’s like 5 tables here what gives??  After we received the check I noticed they applied a gratuity of $8. Excuse me?? It was LUNCH for TWO PEOPLE. I told the hostess I am happy to tip, and always do but to add it to the check for two people is surely a mistake. She confirmed the charge was valid and standard. Ha. Okay.  Hope it was worth it to lose faithful customers over $8 that you would’ve gotten anyways.
Very good food when not so busy...
Love LOVE this place! One of my favorites♥️
Good good

We ordered dinner at 5:30 pm. At 7 I called to check the status of the delivery. The person who answered the phone never asked for my name, simply said “we’re crazy busy! Your order is next! I cannot tell you when!” And hung up. At 7:45, I tried calling again but there was no answer so we cooked dinner. Lo and behold, food was delivered at 8:15, nearly 3 hours after it had been ordered.
Very good food! It took a little while, but the food was hot and fresh. Went here for lunch with a baby. It's not much of a sit down restaurant, but that was perfect for us. The staff was very nice!
The food is always very good, and the ingredients are fresh. The owner is really nice.
Last moment choices is always a bad idea!!
Best Thai food period.
Awesome
Very good crab ragoon. Green curry is good and a little too sweet. Pad Thai  and pad see wu good as well.

Ok believe me when I say I never write stuff on here. I live 10 minutes from this place and never even knew it existed. I pass by it ALL the time. We came across it on Google maps and saw the reviews. Let's just say the reviews aren't lying. Loved it so much. I've had Thai food plenty of times, but when this place asked me if I wanted my food spicy I knew this place was gonna be great! Delicious, will be back again and again and again.
Each meal prepared to order. Great flavor. Great prices.

Great lunch special with entree and appetizers included for a good price. I think the place is more for a take out thing, since the restaurant was empty. I wish there was more staff, since just one guy was doing everything. I recommend the crab rangoons and pad Thai.
First time I  ordered from here, the shrimp was over cooked. I don't think that I would consider ordering again unless I'm in the area.
Awesome. Easy to order online. Good, quality  food.

Pad Thai was great! Made fresh with no use of instant, orange goo sauce many Thai places are using to cut corners....(which contains soy sauce and gluten ingredients that make me sick.) Nice to know there is a place in the neighborhood that does it right!
great food. friendly staffs. nice price!

I ordered Blue Frog through DoorDash delivery. The delivery was earlier than expected and the food was amazing!!! The flavor was so on point. I got the Pad See Ew and my husband got a rice dish. We are definitely going to order from them more.
Intimate setting, friendly staff, good value, flavorful crab Rangoon. Definitely worth a drop in.
Great pad thai.

Love this place! Owner is very attentive and the place is quaint...4 tables and 2 stools at the window counter if you're dining in. Some of my favorites are the Chicken Pad See Ew and the Chicken Pad Woon Sen. The Thai Iced Teas are always tasty!
I liked this spot!  It was right around the corner from where we were staying and we stopped in for Pho.  Very friendly staff.  Took good care  of us.  Would recommend.
NIce people but Definitely NOT authentic Thai food
Probably some of the best food I have had in Bridgeport. Highly recommend stopping by.
Great food

Tried it for the first time and was very impressed. We had the lunch special (available 11-3) which was a great deal. The crab rangoon and veggie egg roll were solid starters. The beef Thai fried rice was rich and flavorful. The green curry on rice was spicy (as desired) and had complex flavors. Overall a solid addition to the neighborhood, not to mention a delicious Thai experience in its own right.

Loved the Green Tea Mochi Ice Cream :) I've also tried the Chicken Basil from here and the flavor is spot on with the perfect amount of spice to make your nose tingle! Will be coming back for quick, tasty Thai food :D
Great Pepper Steak!!!The perfect rice to steak ratio.
Friendly staff

Yummy Thai food in Bridgeport. Is a bit confusing because they still have the archer cafe sign but that is the right place! Highly recommend the pad kee mao or pad see ew with the tom yum soup. Delicious!
